HEADWORD: hideaway
<hw>hideaway</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a hiding place; usually a remote
place used by outlaws.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hideout, den.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an area where one can be alone and
undisturbed.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> retreat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hidebound</ent>⟦br⟧
